  "prompt": "How is it possible to open an account in TD Ameritrade for non-US residents?",
  "response": "Opening a TD Ameritrade account for non-US residents can be challenging, but there are a few options:\n\n1. International Accounts:\n- TD Ameritrade generally requires non-US residents to have a US residential address\n- Some international clients may qualify through specific conditions\n\n2. Requirements typically include:\n- Valid US Social Security Number (SSN)\n- US residential address\n- Valid US government-issued ID\n- Proof of residency in the US\n\n3. Alternative Options:\n- Interactive Brokers often has more flexible international account options\n- Some non-US residents use a US-based friend or relative's address\n- Consider using international brokerage platforms that specialize in cross-border trading\n\n4. Potential Workarounds:\n- Use a US mail forwarding service\n- Establish a US LLC or business entity\n- Consult with a financial advisor specializing in international investing\n\n5. Important Considerations:\n- Tax implications\n- Compliance with US and local financial regulations\n- Potential limitations on certain investment products\n\nRecommendation: Contact TD Ameritrade directly for the most current and specific guidance, as policies can change and individual circumstances vary.\n\nNote: This information is general guidance and not definitive financial advice. Always consult professional financial experts for personalized recommendations.",
